# Copy this file to .env and set the path for your machine.
#
#   cp .env.template .env
#
# .env is gitignored, so your local path stays out of the repo.
#
# WOW_ROOT is the root of your WoW install: the directory that directly contains
# the flavor directories (_retail_, _classic_era_, _classic_, _anniversary_). It
# is not the flavor directory itself, and not Interface/AddOns.
#
# An environment variable of the same name wins over this file, so a one-off run
# can point somewhere else without editing it.
#
# Uncomment exactly one of these, or write your own. Leave the value unquoted.
# Spaces are fine unquoted. Double quotes are not: they apply escape sequences, so
# a Windows path like "C:\new\wow" would come back with a real newline and tab in
# it. Single quotes are safe if you want them.

# Windows, default Battle.net install:
# WOW_ROOT=C:\Program Files (x86)\World of Warcraft

# macOS, default Battle.net install:
# WOW_ROOT=/Applications/World of Warcraft

# Linux, WoW under Wine/Proton via Battle.net (the drive_c prefix will differ):
# WOW_ROOT=/home/you/games/battle-net/drive_c/Program Files (x86)/World of Warcraft
